came Tibullus, then Propertius, whilst he himself closed .

the list as fourth in order from Gallus. A doubt has in· deed been raised as to this interpretation in consequence of the two pronouns iric and illi being used in reference to the same person, viz. Tibullus: but there is no real difficulty in this, for as the subject of the sentence changes
